Lunarpine was at an extreme disadvantage. A Predacon army in an impenetrable
fortressversus a single bot with a bunch  of dummies. (Classic John Wayne
senario.) &quot;You&#39;ll have to come out to get it Predacon.&quot; he said calmly
knowing that the Preds had as much trapped themselves inside the Black
Fortress as kept him out. &quot;And if you fail to produce Silver Scout I&#39;ll have
all my friends reduce you to rubble.&quot;

One bluff had led to another, now all there was to do was add the final
touch. &quot;I hate to inform you that the signals you picked up inside were
faked, We had a unit slip in, plant explosives all through your base and
slip out unnoticed.&quot;

Inside the Black fortress Foxfingers and Razor Claw stood helplessly huddled
beneath Razor Claw forcefield. Lunarpines message broadcast loud and clear
to thier comms. A pannel opened on Foxfingers wrist and the thief pressed in
a sequence that set off one of the charges he&#39;d planted near the base.

With a sudden BOOM that sent debris into the lava pit surrounding the
Fortress.
&quot;That should get thier attention.&quot; Foxfingers comments chuckling the whole
time.

Lunarpine smiled as his scanners picked up the explosion. &quot;They&#39;re alive,&quot;
he thought to himself, &quot;I should&#39;ve known not to doubt them. He returned his
concentration to his comm, &quot;THAT could&#39;ve been the top sections of your
base.&quot; He paused to let the Preds think for a moment. &quot;That WILL be the top
sections of your base if I don&#39;t start seeing some compromises on your
part.&quot; He closed the line cutting off the conversation, The ball was in the
Predacons court now. If there was a civilized answer they would have to
reopen the line to talk.
